Course Content
---------------
Spring Boot
-------------
#1. Spring DataJpa [7/10]
1.1 Why DataJpa
1.2 Working with Jpa Repositories
1.3 Understanding DSL Query Language in writing the queries
1.4 Custom Queries and Parameters
1.5 Pagination & Sort
1.6 Modifiable queries
1.7 Projections
		- Interface-based
		- Class-based projections
		- Dynamic Projections
[MySql Data + Hibernate]

[Mongodb + Spring DataJpa]: not part of the syllabus (bonus)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#2. Spring Boot
1. Introduction to Spring Boot
2. First Spring boot application
3. *** Creating Spring Boot Executable Jar and Inspecting the directory structure
4. How many ways we can create Spring Boot Application
	1. Inheritance Spring Boot Parent Project
	2. Spring Boot Parent (import)
	3. without using parent/import
5. Using @SpringBootApplication annotation
6. SpringApplication.run(), internals of Spring Boot = where does it loads the external configuration of the application.

7. Customizing the Spring Boot Application with Fluent Builder Api
	1. Changing Banner
	2. Turnoff the Banner
7.1 Nested BeanFactories in spring boot

8. Application Events and Application Listeners
9. Command-Line Runners and ApplicationRunners
10. Spring Boot Application Exit
	1. ExitCodeGenerator
	2. ExitCodeExceptionResolver
	3. SpringApplication.exit()
11. Accessing Application Arguments
12. Application properties
	1. properties file
	2. Custom Yaml
13. Configuration Properties
14. Spring Boot Profiles

15. Spring Web MVC Application Flow in Spring Boot
	1. How to deploy as an standalone war application
	2. How to run Spring Mvc Boot application in an embedded servlet container
	3. Registering Servlets and Filters in spring boot
	4. Customizing Embedded Servlet Container
		1. configuration
		2. programmatic

16. Creating our own
	1. autoconfigurations
	2. starter dependencies
17. Spring Boot Actuator endpoints
	1. custom actuator endpoints
18. DevTools

#3. Spring Security
1. Spring WebMvc Security Architecture and Components
2. Compare Spring Security with JEE Security
3. Implement Security for Spring mvc application
	- basic authentication
	- form-based authentication
	- database authentication
4. oauth security
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Java Microservices (using spring framework & spring cloud)
1. Concept of Monolithic application architecture & Microservices based application architecture
2. Patterns of Microservices
	1. Distributed/Global Transactions using (Saga Distributed)
		Choreography-based saga
		Orchestration-based saga
	2. API Composer
	3. Command Query Responsibility Segregation (CQRS)
	4. Database Per Service
3. Implementing Microservices using Spring Cloud and Netflix Tools
	1. Eureka (Discovery Service)
	2. Ribbon (Loadbalancer)
	3. Feign
	4. Spring Circuit Breaker (Resilience4j/Retry)
	5. Spring Cloud Gateway
4. Spring Cloud
	1. Spring Cloud ConfigServer
	2. Spring Cloud ConfigClient
5. Example on Kafka
